data.enText: the posts and rail which you can hold for support when going up or down stairs
to hold on to the banister/banisters

simple_means.memory_skill: ban 禁止 + ister 表人或物 → 禁止入内 → 栏杆

tr: a railing at the side of a staircase or balcony to prevent people from falling

value.def: A banister is a rail supported by posts and fixed along the side of a staircase. The plural banisters can be used to refer to one of these rails.

example.ex: I still remember sliding down the banisters.
example.tran: 我仍然记得从栏杆上滑下来的事。

partsOfSpeech.dec: a 加强 + ban 禁止 + don 给予 → 禁止给 → 放弃
ban 禁止 + al …的 → 被禁止的 → 陈腐的
ban 禁止 + ish 使… → 禁止〔入境〕→ 驱逐
ban 禁止 + ister 表人或物 → 禁止入内 → 栏杆
